Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.05,0:00:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is it true that a Navy ship came?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.67,0:00:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A Navy ship did?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.46,0:00:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I heard that it was\Nanchored here when day broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.30,0:00:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the Navy come...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.14,0:00:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to such a remote island?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.80,0:00:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no one has seen any marines on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.72,0:00:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.14,0:00:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a single person can be found.\NIt's like a ghost ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.44,0:00:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.27,0:00:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Professor!\N--Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.11,0:00:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.28,0:00:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it's nothing to worry about,\Nbut a Navy ship is anchored at the seashore!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.12,0:00:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They might be here for an investigation.\NWe should be cautious, just in case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.62,0:00:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let the scholars know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The raft is finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... you're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.06,0:01:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? You've got\N"I'm lonely" written all over your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.44,0:01:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I was thinking\Nof attaching a flag or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.15,0:01:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll stay here a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.83,0:01:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To sea? So you wanna set out to sea, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.90,0:01:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.71,0:01:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom has been busy with her\Narchaeological research all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.55,0:01:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when she comes back\Nto this island next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.55,0:01:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to ask her to take me with her to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.38,0:01:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I studied hard and I was finally\Nable to become an archaeologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.01,0:01:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An archaeologist? When you're still so small?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.32,0:01:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.98,0:02:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... you don't even remember\Nyour mom's face, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.65,0:02:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right... but she's still my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.32,0:02:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.41,0:02:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Say, Saul...\N--Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.58,0:02:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know that the world has a blank history\Nof 100 years that no one knows about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.37,0:02:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's called the "Blank Century."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.42,0:02:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious about it, but the Government\Nprohibits people from investigating, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.17,0:02:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I heard that my mom is traveling\Naround the world investigating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.43,0:02:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't tell anyone about it,\Nsince it's actually a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.25,0:02:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Could it mean that she's traveling in\Nsearch of those stones called Poneglyphs?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.94,0:02:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you know about Poneglyphs?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.78,0:02:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do! But don't talk\Nabout it in front of people, okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.99,0:02:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention, about your\Nmom traveling in search of... Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.33,0:02:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.79,0:03:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin... Do you know your mom's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.29,0:03:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.42,0:03:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Nico Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.49,0:03:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saul?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.10,0:03:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin is Olvia's daughter...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.15,0:03:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... could this place be...\Nan island called Ohara?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.40,0:03:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah.\N--Ahh! This is terrible! Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I drifted to Ohara?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to be sitting around talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.92,0:03:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Robin!\N--What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.33,0:03:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This might shock you, but listen to me carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.38,0:03:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Navy battleships should be\Nheaded to Ohara right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.17,0:03:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Navy? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.05,0:03:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to eliminate the scholars on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.61,0:03:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.27,0:04:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That's a lie...\N--Don't tell the Government you're a scholar!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.74,0:04:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That's a lie...!\N--Got that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.19,0:04:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! I'd never lie to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.22,0:04:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to town now and see if anything\Nstrange has been happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible your mom might be back, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.46,0:04:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.67,0:04:26.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Get running, get running,\Nholding our flag high in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.77,0:04:38.79,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's cross this endless sea to go in search of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.79,0:04:44.80,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,a global miracle no one\Nhas yet been able to find
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:49.68,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,With our hearts pounding,\Nwe'll just charge ahead as we please
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:55.56,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,following the footprints of\Nthose who chase their dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.39,0:05:02.36,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how stormy the night,\Nif we join our hearts as one,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:06.61,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,we will be able to make it through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.61,0:05:07.90,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Always!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:14.58,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Get running, get running,\Nholding our flag high in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:20.55,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though there are tears\Nwe don't want anyone to see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.55,0:05:26.59,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase it, chase it,\Nif we want to achieve our dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.59,0:05:29.18,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,we should always look\Nstraight ahead without fear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:31.49,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't stop here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.49,0:05:34.51,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.51,0:05:35.77,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Start me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:44.51,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Get running, get running,\Nhead past everyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:50.58,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So long as we don't run from it,\Nwe can grasp tomorrow in our hands
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:56.54,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase it, chase it,\Neverything we see before us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:06:01.33,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's carve it into the blank pages of our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.65,0:06:04.34,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Brand New World
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.54,0:06:05.76,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Start me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fated Mother and Daughter!\NThe Mother's Name Is Olvia!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.21,0:06:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Olvia...\N--Olvia-san...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was you who came on that Navy ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought you had been caught by the Navy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.78,0:06:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry that I came back bearing bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.13,0:06:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what I just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the government has finally\Nset its sights on Ohara?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you read the newspaper?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.55,0:06:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Poneglyph search team that set off\Nfrom Ohara six years ago was annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:07:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them except for me...\NA total of 33 members...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.27,0:07:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was also temporarily captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.77,0:07:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The government evaluated\Nmy fellow scholars' belongings
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and figured out that we came from Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.71,0:07:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is inexcusable! To think that this\Nisland is now in danger because of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.58,0:07:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! It's no one's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.35,0:07:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who set out to sea and those\Nwho stayed here--we're all one team!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you guys who experienced a terrible time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We put you through a terrible ordeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.30,0:07:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.97,0:07:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ohara is a place where talented\Nscholars from all around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.19,0:07:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gather and continue to study history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Government has been\Nconsidering us a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They must be thinking that they\Nfinally found something on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.53,0:07:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not gonna pass up this opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but we were able to get\Nthat information without delay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.95,0:08:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, everyone in Ohara who\Nclaims to be a scholar will be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, everyone, get out of Ohara immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.33,0:08:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... This time, we probably won't\Nbe able to slip past their investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.49,0:08:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like we usually do...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...if they are trying to kill us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, hurry up and...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, Olvia...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.97,0:08:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't run away leaving this\Ntreasure of mankind behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We feel the same way, Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.12,0:08:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.78,0:08:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what the Government is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we run, the precious history\Nthat exists here won't be protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.41,0:08:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll try whatever we can,\Njust like we always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.25,0:08:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...there must be something\Nweighing on your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.69,0:08:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.96,0:08:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make up your mind, Olvia! Are you\Ngonna come aboard the ship or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.09,0:08:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have a lingering attachment\Nto your child, don't come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.62,0:08:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is about your husband's\Nunfinished business, we will...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'll come with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a scholar from Ohara. I can't\Nabandon our predecessors' will!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.74,0:09:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll solve all the mysteries\Nand come back for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy... Where's Mommy?\NWhere did Mommy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.54,0:09:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom set out to sea for work.\NYou'll stay here with us for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're noisy! Be quiet or I'll hit you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.71,0:09:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop it. She's only two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our daughter is two, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.71,0:09:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care whether she's your\Nbig sister's child or whatever--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how dare you take in such a burden?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?! Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.40,0:09:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um... I... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.56,0:09:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.31,0:10:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you wanna read books, just let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.70,0:10:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have money, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.88,0:10:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to pay.\NYou can read them all for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Free?\N--Yeah, since this is the best library in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.34,0:10:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The best one in the world?\N--That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, you're Olvia's daughter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.47,0:10:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like books?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.06,0:10:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks just like you did\Nwhen you were a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And like you were at that age,\Nshe's a rare genius, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.03,0:10:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So long as I know she's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.88,0:10:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've stepped into this line of work.\NSo I have to give up my attachment to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.48,0:10:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since I can't make her a "criminal's daughter."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Clover! This time, a ship flying\Nthe World Government's flag has come!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.12,0:10:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Government ship has come\Nall the way to the West Blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.08,0:10:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It indeed seems quite serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:11:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys and I are neither fellow\Nscholars nor acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.85,0:11:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep that in mind... no matter what happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.43,0:11:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Olvia! What're you going to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.40,0:11:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let the headquarters know\Nthat we arrived at our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.88,0:11:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go, go, go! Keep on moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... What a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.32,0:11:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, this work'd\Nbetter get me a promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.49,0:11:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, go get all the scholars and restrain them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.27,0:11:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What's going on?!\N--A woman with a gun is running around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.10,0:11:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Heaven's sake! I'm sorry, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Admiral Kuzan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:11:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.98,0:12:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been notified that CP9's\NChief Spandine has arrived in Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.90,0:12:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is that something so important\Nthat you had to wake me up to tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.49,0:12:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Robin?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did my mom come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you saying? There's no way\Nthat your mother is in Ohara, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to give up my attachment to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since I can't make her a "criminal's daughter."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.11,0:12:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.33,0:12:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.82,0:12:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right! There's trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that Navy battleships\Nare coming to this island
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.91,0:12:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to capture all\Nthe scholars on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.38,0:13:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a disturbance or\Nsomething happening in town?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.73,0:13:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.43,0:13:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard that a Government\Nship just came to this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll probably be a more\Nrigorous investigation than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Robin. Even if the\NGovernment people come,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't tell them you're an\Narchaeologist no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're small, no one will think\Nthat you're a scholar. Got that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.28,0:13:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of our way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop what you're doing!\NGet outside with your hands in the air!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.75,0:13:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're being quite violent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Ohara lab is suspected of a\Nserious crime--deciphering Poneglyphs!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.55,0:13:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It requires a thorough search,\Nso all of you, go outside immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treat this place with care.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.64,0:13:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The value of everything in here\Nis beyond your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have to listen to what you say!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take them outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.06,0:13:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.42,0:14:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To all the townspeople!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.19,0:14:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We now suspect that this island's scholars\Nare devils who wish to destroy the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're world-class scholars\Nand the pride of this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.16,0:14:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consequently, we'll conduct a\Nlarge-scale search of the entire island!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.59,0:14:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During that time, those who have\Nnothing to do with archaeology
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are expected to take an ID with them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and temporarily take refuge on the\Nevacuation ship at the west seashore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.63,0:14:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An evacuation ship?!\NWhy are you going that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the scholars' problem,\Nwe have nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.51,0:14:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So there should be no need\Nfor us to leave the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.80,0:14:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our duty to pass that message to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.83,0:14:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens later\Nto those who ignore our advice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's none of our concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Leave town!\N--Evacuate to the west seashore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.53,0:14:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The World Government is up to something!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.66,0:14:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahhh! I got shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is it for me! I'm a goner, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.54,0:15:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the top... that I want my son\Nto take over the position of chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief, please take a close look.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.30,0:15:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bullet just went through\Nthe sleeve of your jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.17,0:15:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't miss next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.00,0:15:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well... To think that a heinous\Ncriminal who splendidly escaped
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.23,0:15:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Navy's prison is coincidentally\Nvisiting this island... Nico Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You kept denying your connection to\Nthe Ohara scholars, and yet, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.53,0:15:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems as if you're declaring\Nthat this is your hometown...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.95,0:15:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That the scholars here are committing\Nthe same crime that you guys were.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.58,0:15:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My being here alone isn't proof of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you have all sorts of\Nexcuses ready. You're a smart woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.88,0:15:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your connection to Ohara\Ndoesn't need to be proved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.47,0:16:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we dig through every nook and corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.31,0:16:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,evidence of your research on\NPoneglyphs will turn up in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.44,0:16:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Government thinks that\Nthe probability of this is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.69,0:16:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being able to capture you guys,\Nwho were on the run for six long years,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.27,0:16:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just gave the Government a small push.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are plenty of Poneglyph\Nresearchers around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.86,0:16:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each time we captured one, we always\Nsearched for their connection to Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.54,0:16:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... In order to\Nuse Ohara as a warning...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly! If Ohara, the holy land\Nof archaeology, is crushed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.48,0:16:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'll send shockwaves throughout academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.76,0:16:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can make the world realize
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.47,0:16:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what happens to those who\Nresearch the "Blank Century."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.39,0:16:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the battleships from Headquarters\Nunder standby order are...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.00,0:16:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa... Just how much do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're used to ensure that not\Neven a single criminal escapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:17:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But as a matter of form,\Nwe need to verify the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we're not pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.70,0:17:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I came all the way here to conduct\Na compulsory investigation on the island
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.04,0:17:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to send off those who have\Nnothing to do with the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I came all this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.12,0:17:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.15,0:17:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop it! The books\Nhere are a world treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.09,0:17:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still someone here? Take him outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.02,0:17:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Come!\N--Dammit, you bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.52,0:17:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be a hidden room!\NMake sure we find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.59,0:17:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The battleships are already within sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.03,0:17:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this all of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, gather all the scholars here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.27,0:17:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. The scholars have been captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:18:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth did they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said that the goal of the scholars'\Nresearch is to destroy the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.85,0:18:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.16,0:18:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the evacuation ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's at the west seashore! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.31,0:18:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and go! Hurry to the west seashore!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.73,0:18:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin... It seems that\Nthere's an evacuation ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.40,0:18:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can no longer tell what\Nthe Government will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.22,0:18:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hurry up and go there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Even if I get on that ship,\Nthere won't be nice people!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.04,0:18:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stay here with you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.37,0:18:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Robin...\N--Just like you guys, I'm a--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.70,0:18:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys working hard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.06,0:18:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for taking the\Ntrouble to come here, Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.23,0:18:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I didn't expect that a ferocious\Nanimal would appear on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.89,0:18:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was nearly killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.01,0:18:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olvia...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olvia-san...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.62,0:18:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, listen carefully.\NThis woman is an escaped prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:18:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The group she belonged to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.69,0:19:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was recently eliminated for the crime\Nof deciphering the ancient texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.55,0:19:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, we still don't know the ringleader.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.75,0:19:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you guys are connected to this woman,\Nit'll make matters quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How terrible of them to hurt a woman like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.47,0:19:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin, go to the evacuation ship. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.25,0:19:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.61,0:19:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.38,0:19:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...grown so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.82,0:19:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olvia...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.73,0:19:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What have they done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have they no respect for the library?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that they'd take\Nsuch drastic measures...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.95,0:19:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa... They've made a big show.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.71,0:19:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Click.\N--Hello? Is this the Chief?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.42,0:20:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.91,0:20:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a secret room in the basement,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.14,0:20:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in there, we found a huge stone\Nthat's probably a Poneglyph
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.59,0:20:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and research documents clearly\Ndiscussing the ancient texts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.95,0:20:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.20,0:20:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Click.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.52,0:20:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, scholars of Ohara!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your death sentence has now been decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.25,0:20:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's indeed regrettable...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.92,0:20:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that the world's best archaeologists\Nlose their lives together today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.75,0:20:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? What a letdown. That was all I had to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.72,0:20:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing I have left to do is\Nreport this to the Five Elder Stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.92,0:20:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.96,0:20:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor! Are they really gonna\Nkill all of you?! That's a lie, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.16,0:20:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they do that just because\Nyou read the ancient texts...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! You brat! The purpose of their\Nresearch is to revive a powerful weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.26,0:20:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and commit mass murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.32,0:20:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true! They aren't\Nthinking about anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.00,0:21:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin, stop it. It's pointless to discuss\Nthe matter with an errand boy like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.49,0:21:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.49,0:21:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really the weapon itself that\Nthe Government is afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.14,0:21:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Professor!\N--Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's connected, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.29,0:21:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--This is good timing.\N--Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.26,0:21:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me speak to the Five Elder Stars,\Nthe world's leaders, before I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.11,0:21:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We, the scholars at Ohara, have continued\Nour research for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and although the research isn't completed yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.45,0:21:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we formed a hypothesis\Nabout the "Blank Century."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.72,0:21:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'd like to report it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.92,0:21:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What rubbish...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.30,0:21:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey.\N--Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.61,0:21:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin, get out of here immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.43,0:21:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listening to what I'm about to say is a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.98,0:21:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.85,0:21:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it seems like the scholars\Nhave been found guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.84,0:21:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.34,0:21:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Navy battleships are moving\Ntoward here from the eastern sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.41,0:21:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna do something!\NLet's hurry to the evacuation ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.58,0:21:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a giant!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.40,0:22:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, Robin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Escape from this island right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.04,0:22:17.14,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We fight harder against\Nthe wall that confronts us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.14,0:22:21.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We charge ahead stronger\Nwith overflowing power
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.06,0:22:25.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't fear even if we\Nhave to give up everything
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.19,0:22:28.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's all to ensure we smile in the end
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.61,0:22:31.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll become No. 1
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.45,0:22:33.32,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll aim for freedom in wonderland
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.32,0:22:35.53,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, there's a faint light\Nshowing us the road to tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.53,0:22:37.70,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,an era created by risking everything
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.70,0:22:39.83,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We always try our best, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.83,0:22:41.83,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we want to achieve glory,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.83,0:22:43.21,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,now is the time--don't be afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:45.13,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll surely win the future\Ntogether with friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.13,0:22:49.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we start running faster\Ntowards the vast world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.09,0:22:53.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We can take off with unknown powers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.09,0:22:55.35,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't fear, and we don't waver
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.35,0:22:59.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens,\Nin the end we'll surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.06,0:23:03.10,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We fight harder against\Nthe wall that confronts us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.10,0:23:07.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We charge ahead stronger\Nwith overflowing power
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.07,0:23:11.32,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't fear even if we\Nhave to give up everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.32,0:23:13.32,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Charge ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.32,0:23:15.20,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start running towards tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.20,0:23:18.20,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's all to ensure we smile in the end
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saul, please take care of Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let my daughter\Nescape from here at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.97,0:23:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! What about you, Mom?!\NAren't you gonna come with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.05,0:23:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still something\Nthat I have to do here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.74,0:23:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I don't wanna be separated!\NI was finally able to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.27,0:23:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.05,0:23:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.73,0:23:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Tragedy of Ohara!\NThe Terror of Buster Call"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.67,0:23:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
